<br>
If the car designers said &quot;90 % of the people want to buy Cars, not trucks or SUVs or Minivans, we should devote 90 % of our resources to that.&quot; it would be a fair comparison.<br>
<br>
The best business decision is going to be the one that keeps the majority of your users the happiest. I'd much prefer that they focus the majority of their efforts balancing the 50+ game because honestly, that's where most players are playing.<br>
<br>
Low end balance is ONLY out of whack due to twinking and the trickle down economy. If VI would simply let new focus items, flowing thought pieces, and other such items become tradeable, they would solve the problem, that's true. VI doesn't like twinking though, so I highly doubt you'll ever see this sort of thing go into effect. <br>
<br>
By the way, at level 30 (about a month after Kunark came out) I was doing much better than any non-twinked melee I ran into. I could solo all day without issue, and I never had mana issues in experience groups. I thought it was rather unfair that a warrior couldn't run across frontier mountains safely whereas I could solo there all day long without ever being touched.  <p><table border="0" width="111">
