<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Good</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
    Verant's attititude and admission (finally) that Caster's need to be examined vis a vis the melee equipment improvements.  Getting them to admit and look at the problem seemed impossible a year ago and finally it looks that it may actually happen!<br>
<br>
     The &quot;Ancient Spells&quot; are a great idea.  The damage/mana ratio on the new ice spell is amazing.  &quot;Rare&quot; spell drops are something that I have seen the Uber folk ask for countless times and its good to see that something truely useful for Uber casters will drop.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Bad</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
     Level 60 is where Wizards need the least work.  We have a useful and sometimes essential function on raids that actually fits with ourt class definition.  Given the already numerous and incredible spells at 60 (Sunstrike, Icy Spear, banes) one must wonder why two more were added here first.<br>
<br>
     The &quot;Mudflation&quot;/Twink problem is accute from 1-60.  Try grouping with a &quot;Tank&quot; in Oasis at level 18 and watch him do more damage in one swing than you can do with a DD spell.  Watch him continue to do it when you go OOM.  This begs the question, what will be done 1-59?  Will 1-59 truley be addressed, or will they be ignored?  This is a very real concern.  Remember that we had 14 threads during the Class Balance discussions and the only suggestion implmented was the level 60 Banes.  ALL INT CASTERS MUST BE EXAMINED FROM 1-60!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Ugly</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
     Where are the focus items?  Verant makes no mention of them here.  Focus items would be an excellent way to increase mana regeneration, lower mana cost and increase damage output, across the board, without adding any new spells.  Focus Items <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> do not mean</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Flowing Thought 2 items which drop from semi-uber mobs.<br>
<br>
      Will anything be done to &quot;fix&quot; the sustained damage output over time problem which results in Wizards having a hard time finding pick-up groups?  Time will tell.<br>
<br>
     A good start, I'm hopeful, VI must address 1-60, not just 60! <p>Norrath: Torcer Arcana - Level 58 Wizard - The Nameless<Br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/27/02 5:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yawn</span><hr size=1> Well, that they are at last admitting there is a problem is good...but an elitist solution, rather than a solution for all, is bad.<br>
